# Cursor Rules - Frontend App

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript strictly — no `any` types
- Functional components only, hooks for all state
- Named exports preferred over default exports
- File names: PascalCase for components, camelCase for utils

## React Patterns
- Extract business logic into custom hooks
- Keep components under 150 lines; split if larger
- Use React.memo() for expensive list items
- Prefer composition over prop drilling

## State Management
- Local state: useState/useReducer
- Server state: React Query (useQuery/useMutation)
- Global UI state: Zustand (if needed)
- Avoid Redux unless the team agrees

## Testing
- Test behavior, not implementation
- One test file per component/hook
- Use `userEvent` over `fireEvent` for interactions
- Mock at the boundary (API calls), not internals

## Performance
- Lazy load routes with React.lazy()
- Memoize only when profiler shows it helps
- Avoid inline object/function creation in render
